<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="692" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/249: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Callao-Lima</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Handley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-20T09:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">May 20,
                                            1919, 9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        4.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Referring to my telegram of May 12, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d692fn1">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <p>The presidential election vote Sunday and Monday in Callao-Lima
                                Province gave Leguia large majority. Present indications incomplete
                                returns from other provinces have elected him President of Peru.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Handley</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>